title.narrative: Mine Closure, Environment & Socio-Economic Regeneration Project

description.narrative: The Project Development Objectives (PDO) in the Loan Agreement is to strengthen the government's ability to undertake mining sector reform by (i) building MEC's capacity for closing uneconomic mining enterprises through support for closing complex mines and ancillary facilities in an environmentally sustainable manner; and (ii) providing support to mining communities and local public authorities for socio-economic regeneration of the mining regions through central entities."

condition.narrative: All agreed social subcomponents to be implemented in accordance with the operating manuals for each subcomponent.
Establish subsidy monitoring system and report by Oct 31 each year on the level of budgetary support provided to the miningcompanies.
Institutional strengthening and management of AZM, including approval of new management.
MEC take actions to improve tailings management at identified mines and provide Bank with a report on the results of actions
Measures required under EMPs, Environmental Frameworks and Land Compensaion/Resettlement Framework to be implemented in a timelymanner
